programme.sub-title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Battles are almost always about territory. Advancing the front line, seizing the port, the city, the oil field. The fate of nations in the war rose and fell on battles that took territory. Singapore, Monte Casino, Stalingrad...all about territory.
programme.series-desc: Every battle is both a victory and a defeat; it depends which flag you fly. The battles of World War II were decided not only by strategy but by armies in their element. These battles won and lost would determine the course of the future.

programme.title: Impossible Peace
programme.desc: Exchange rates and floundering economies were not the only things influencing how and where people lived. The motor-car and other technological advances were transformative, though some clung tight to the past...
programme.series-desc: Two world wars tore the heart out of the twentieth century. Between these wars was an age that is viewed as a time of jazz, prohibition, the talkies, radio and the motor car. A time that, in reality, was an age of anxiety. A peace that failed.

programme.title: The First World War
programme.desc: The war at sea was every bit as bitter as the war on land. The battle at Jutland proved inconclusive, but the U-Boat menace threatened Britain as never before. Meanwhile, America entered the war.
programme.series-desc: This stunning account of WW1 offers new interpretations of and insights into one of the defining events of the twentieth century. It offers a truly global vision of a war that is so often misconceived as a prolonged skirmish on the Western Front.

programme.series-desc: In this six part series mechanic, motorcycle racer and engineering enthusiast Guy Martin celebrates the workers of Britain's Industrial Revolution by getting stuck into six of the country's biggest restoration project.

programme.title: The Complete Story of Hitler and the Nazis
programme.sub-title: The Complete Hitler and the Nazis

programme.series-desc: The murderous deeds of Hitler’s Third Reich are still widely recalled today, but what is less well known is the strange concoction of beliefs that underpinned the Nazi regime.

programme.series-desc: Have you ever wondered what life was like for Vikings or WWII “squaddies?” Alex Jordan follows a group of weekend battle reenactors in this glorious celebration of British eccentricity.

programme.title: Gallipoli
programme.desc: Massive German howitzers are brought to the front line as the British Commanders race against the clock to withdraw troops.
programme.series-desc: As dawn breaks on the 25th April, 1915, Anzac troops go into battle on the beaches of the Gallipoli peninsula in Turkey.

programme.title: Navy SEALs: Untold Stories

programme.title: Sea Power
programme.desc: The best way to attack an enemy ship would be from beneath. This lead to the building of one of the most significant weapons of the second World War — the German U-boat.
programme.series-desc: This documentary series dives deep into the development and creation of the world's most important nautical warships.

programme.title: Under Siege
programme.desc: The grim, powerful story of the "Hero City" that lost one million of its citizens as it steadfastly withstood a 900-day German siege.
programme.series-desc: This docu-miniseries explores siege warfare and explains how those that are vastly outnumbered have stood behind walls and barricades in a last stand against their attackers.

programme.title: The First World War
programme.desc: Over 1 million German troops were committed to Kaiserschlacht, the last great offensive of the War while conflict still raged on many other fronts
programme.series-desc: This stunning account of WW1 offers new interpretations of and insights into one of the defining events of the twentieth century. It offers a truly global vision of a war that is so often misconceived as a prolonged skirmish on the Western Front.

programme.title: Weapons Race
programme.desc: Discover the weapons race which continued with the Soviet Union using every means possible – particularly espionage - to catch up with the United States, and then competing to produce smaller and more deadly bombs.
programme.series-desc: Examine the development of new military technologies and how their evolution impacted tactics and strategies used in warfare from the High Middle Ages to the Modern Era.

programme.title: Battleplan
programme.desc: Flank attack – going around the side of the enemy instead of taking him head-on – is one of the most basic of Battleplans, yet stories of key victories decided by a flanking manoeuvres fill military textbooks.
programme.series-desc: Examine the history of military tactics, from blitzkrieg to blockade, raiding operations to strategic bombing and on to guerrilla warfare.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.sub-title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The second world war was a conflict on an unprecedented scale. Its battles set new marks for the sheer size of forces deployed and for the power of their weapons. In this episode, we study the first battle at sea, and the largest army to have ever marched
programme.series-desc: Every battle is both a victory and a defeat; it depends which flag you fly. The battles of World War II were decided not only by strategy but by armies in their element. These battles won and lost would determine the course of the future.
